<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="48" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,259,789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,439,464]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[327,531,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nearctica">
<emphasis box="[327,531,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Drusilla nearctica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[804,897,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ashei">
<emphasis box="[804,897,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">D. ashei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be confidently separated by the following male characters: shape of the median lobe (
<figureCitation box="[686,821,476,500]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 19" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[181,1397,421,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[168,1418,411,1895]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 19. Male genitalia of Drusilla ashei (12 – 15) and D. nearctica (16 – 19). 12, 16) aedeagus, lateral; 13, 17) aedeagus, parameral; 14, 18) paramere, outer lateral; 15, 19) apex of apical lobe of paramere, inner lateral. Scale bars (0.1 mm): I = 12 – 14, 16 – 18; II = 15, 19." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210862/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Figs. 
<number box="[751,821,476,500]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="16.5" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="16.0">16–17</number>
</figureCitation>
); distal apodeme short, less than four times as long as its width (
<figureCitation box="[262,345,511,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 19" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[181,1397,421,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[168,1418,411,1895]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 19. Male genitalia of Drusilla ashei (12 – 15) and D. nearctica (16 – 19). 12, 16) aedeagus, lateral; 13, 17) aedeagus, parameral; 14, 18) paramere, outer lateral; 15, 19) apex of apical lobe of paramere, inner lateral. Scale bars (0.1 mm): I = 12 – 14, 16 – 18; II = 15, 19." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210862/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[314,345,511,535]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
); aedeagal costal morphology of parameral surface (
<figureCitation box="[929,1011,511,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 19" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[181,1397,421,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[168,1418,411,1895]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 19. Male genitalia of Drusilla ashei (12 – 15) and D. nearctica (16 – 19). 12, 16) aedeagus, lateral; 13, 17) aedeagus, parameral; 14, 18) paramere, outer lateral; 15, 19) apex of apical lobe of paramere, inner lateral. Scale bars (0.1 mm): I = 12 – 14, 16 – 18; II = 15, 19." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210862/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[981,1011,511,535]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
); paramere with velum obscuring apical lobe in outer lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[486,569,548,572]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 19" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[181,1397,421,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[168,1418,411,1895]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 19. Male genitalia of Drusilla ashei (12 – 15) and D. nearctica (16 – 19). 12, 16) aedeagus, lateral; 13, 17) aedeagus, parameral; 14, 18) paramere, outer lateral; 15, 19) apex of apical lobe of paramere, inner lateral. Scale bars (0.1 mm): I = 12 – 14, 16 – 18; II = 15, 19." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210862/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[538,569,548,572]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
); chaetotaxy of parameral apical lobe (
<figureCitation box="[1005,1088,548,572]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 19" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[181,1397,421,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[168,1418,411,1895]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 19. Male genitalia of Drusilla ashei (12 – 15) and D. nearctica (16 – 19). 12, 16) aedeagus, lateral; 13, 17) aedeagus, parameral; 14, 18) paramere, outer lateral; 15, 19) apex of apical lobe of paramere, inner lateral. Scale bars (0.1 mm): I = 12 – 14, 16 – 18; II = 15, 19." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210862/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[1057,1088,548,572]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="50" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,259,789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,583,608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Description.</emphasis>
Body (
<figureCitation box="[433,501,583,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1962,1985]" captionTargetBox="[174,1413,772,1939]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[174,1413,772,1941]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Holotypes of Drusilla. Dorsal habitus: 1) D. nearctica; 2) D. ashei. 3) D. nearctica lateral view of head and thorax." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210859/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[489,501,583,607]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) length on average 
<quantity box="[738,827,583,607]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" unit="mm" value="3.3">3.3 mm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[845,988,583,607]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.35" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="3.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" unit="mm" value="3.35" valueMax="3.6" valueMin="3.1">3.1–3.6 mm</quantity>
, n = 
<number box="[1052,1083,583,607]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="10.0">10</number>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[1106,1162,583,607]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Hind</collectingCountry>
wings degenerated and absent. Body color with head, pronotum, elytra and most of abdomen dark brown; usually most (if partial, mediobasal portion) of abdominal tergite VI black; frequently tergites V, VII and VIII brown to approaching black and usually not as dark as tergite VI; segments III–IV sometimes with a small basal portion of tergal disk approaching brown compared with rest of given segment; abdominal sternites usually corresponding with tergites in overall color patterning amongst segments; antennae, legs and mouthparts yellowish-brown to brown.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210860/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" targetBox="[197,1388,858,1905]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1934,1987]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,307,1934,1957]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">FIGURES 4–5</emphasis>
