<taxonomicName box="[471,656,1934,1956]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nearctica">
<emphasis box="[471,656,1934,1956]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Drusilla nearctica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 4) prementum, ventral; 5) right maxilla, ventral. Scale bars (0.1 mm): I = 5; II = 4.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210861/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" targetBox="[194,1389,190,1623]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1664,1748]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
