. Mouthparts of 
<taxonomicName box="[483,669,1664,1687]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nearctica">
<emphasis box="[483,669,1664,1687]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">Drusilla nearctica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 6) labrum; 7) epipharynx; 8) left mandible, ventral; 9) right mandible, dorsal; 10) mentum, ventral; 11) left antenna, inner surface with dorsal surface facing down the page. Scale bars (0.1 mm): I = 11; II = 8–9; III = 6–7, 10.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1792,2033]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
Head subcircular (HW = 
<quantity box="[482,583,1792,1816]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.699999999999999" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="0.47">0.47 mm</quantity>
, 
<quantity box="[595,761,1792,1816]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.75" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="4.699999999999999" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="0.475" valueMax="0.48" valueMin="0.47">0.47–0.48 mm</quantity>
; HL = 
<quantity box="[839,942,1792,1816]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="0.48">0.48 mm</quantity>
, 
<quantity box="[953,1119,1792,1816]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.85" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.699999999999999" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="0.485" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.47">0.47–0.50 mm</quantity>
; HW/HL = 
<number box="[1251,1303,1792,1816]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="0.98">0.98</number>
, 
<number box="[1315,1366,1792,1816]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="0.94">0.94</number>
–1.00) with faint imbricate microsculpture; eyes small and occupying approximately a third of head length (OL = 
<number box="[1380,1432,1828,1852]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="0.16">0.16</number>
, 
<quantity box="[151,319,1864,1888]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="0.16" valueMax="0.17" valueMin="0.15">0.15–0.17 mm</quantity>
; OL/HL = 
<number box="[447,499,1864,1888]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="0.34">0.34</number>
, 
<number box="[512,629,1864,1888]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="0.32499999999999996" valueMax="0.35" valueMin="0.3">0.30–0.35</number>
); setae on vertex directed posteriomedially; labrum (
<figureCitation box="[1230,1299,1864,1888]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1664,1687]" captionTargetBox="[194,1389,190,1623]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[184,1403,177,1641]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 10. Mouthparts of Drusilla nearctica. 6) labrum; 7) epipharynx; 8) left mandible, ventral; 9) right mandible, dorsal; 10) mentum, ventral; 11) left antenna, inner surface with dorsal surface facing down the page. Scale bars (0.1 mm): I = 11; II = 8 – 9; III = 6 – 7, 10." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210861/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[1284,1299,1864,1888]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
) with distal seta 
<number box="[202,216,1900,1924]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="2.0">2</number>
(ds 
<number box="[258,273,1900,1924]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="2.0">2</number>
) posterior of medial setae; epipharynx (
<figureCitation box="[724,792,1900,1924]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1664,1687]" captionTargetBox="[194,1389,190,1623]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[184,1403,177,1641]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 10. Mouthparts of Drusilla nearctica. 6) labrum; 7) epipharynx; 8) left mandible, ventral; 9) right mandible, dorsal; 10) mentum, ventral; 11) left antenna, inner surface with dorsal surface facing down the page. Scale bars (0.1 mm): I = 11; II = 8 – 9; III = 6 – 7, 10." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210861/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[777,792,1900,1924]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) with a generalized athetine form; maxillary (
<figureCitation box="[1310,1377,1900,1924]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[197,1388,858,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[185,1402,844,1913]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 5. Mouthparts of Drusilla nearctica. 4) prementum, ventral; 5) right maxilla, ventral. Scale bars (0.1 mm): I = 5; II = 4." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210860/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[1363,1377,1900,1924]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
) lacinia with a distal comb consisting of approximately five spines, palpomere IV subulate with filamentous sensillae that are fitted against segment, palpomere IV distally lacking an apical process; labial palpus (
<figureCitation box="[1200,1267,1972,1996]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[197,1388,858,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[185,1402,844,1913]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 5. Mouthparts of Drusilla nearctica. 4) prementum, ventral; 5) right maxilla, ventral. Scale bars (0.1 mm): I = 5; II = 4." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210860/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[1252,1267,1972,1996]" pageId="4" pageNumber="49" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
) lacking setula β and δ, see generic diagnosis for a further description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,968]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
Pronotum slightly transverse (PW = 
<quantity box="[613,717,151,175]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="0.54">0.54 mm</quantity>
, 
<quantity box="[729,895,151,175]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.35" metricValueMax="5.6" metricValueMin="5.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="0.535" valueMax="0.56" valueMin="0.51">0.51–0.56 mm</quantity>
; PL = 
<quantity box="[972,1076,151,175]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="0.48">0.48 mm</quantity>
, 
<quantity box="[1087,1254,151,175]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" metricValueMax="5.1" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="0.48" valueMax="0.51" valueMin="0.45">0.45–0.51 mm</quantity>
; PW/PL = 
<number box="[1380,1432,151,175]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="1.12">1.12</number>
, 
<number box="[151,264,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="1.13" valueMax="1.17" valueMin="1.09">1.09–1.17</number>
) with faint imbricate microsculpture; three pairs of macrosetae present, consisting of one apical pair and two lateral pairs anterior of horizontal midline.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,968]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
Elytra, together, transverse (EW = 
<number box="[588,640,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="0.59">0.59</number>
, 
<quantity box="[650,816,260,284]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="6.3" metricValueMin="5.699999999999999" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="0.6" valueMax="0.63" valueMin="0.57">0.57–0.63 mm</quantity>
; EL = 
<number box="[890,941,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="0.44">0.44</number>
, 
<quantity box="[953,1119,260,284]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.35" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="4.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="0.435" valueMax="0.45" valueMin="0.42">0.42–0.45 mm</quantity>
; EW/EL = 
<number box="[1244,1296,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="1.36">1.36</number>
, 
<number box="[1307,1423,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="1.3399999999999999" valueMax="1.41" valueMin="1.27">1.27–1.41</number>
); each elytron broadly rounded with posterior-most extension medially; elytron with pleural surface forming an approximate right angle with disk; disk with longitudinal basolateral impression; disk of elytron with conspicuously stronger and more irregularly imbricate microsculpture compared with head and pronotum; macroseta on each elytron at subapicolateral margin on dorsal surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,968]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
Abdomen with dorsal surface subglabrous; tergite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[854,939,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1468,1491]" captionTargetBox="[164,1418,202,1445]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[158,1428,193,1457]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 25. Details of Drusilla nearctica (20 – 23) and D. ashei (24 – 25). 20) tergite VIII; 21) sternite VIII; 22) female genital segments (tergites IX and X), showing genital plate and spermathecal duct, dorsal; 23) spermatheca; 24) male genital segments (sternite IX and tergites IX and X), dorsal; 25) detail of sternite IX, ventral. Scale bars (0.1 mm): I = 20 – 22, 24 – 25." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210863/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
Fig. 
<number box="[910,939,439,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
) with apical margin sinuate, resulting in a broad medial and acute lateral projections; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[787,869,476,500]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1468,1491]" captionTargetBox="[164,1418,202,1445]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[158,1428,193,1457]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 25. Details of Drusilla nearctica (20 – 23) and D. ashei (24 – 25). 20) tergite VIII; 21) sternite VIII; 22) female genital segments (tergites IX and X), showing genital plate and spermathecal duct, dorsal; 23) spermatheca; 24) male genital segments (sternite IX and tergites IX and X), dorsal; 25) detail of sternite IX, ventral. Scale bars (0.1 mm): I = 20 – 22, 24 – 25." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210863/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
Fig. 
<number box="[840,869,476,500]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
) with a blunt medial apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,968]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
Males with vertex of head variably impressed. Pronotum variably, medially impressed. Median lobe ovular in lateral (
<figureCitation box="[236,317,548,572]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 19" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[181,1397,421,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[168,1418,411,1895]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 19. Male genitalia of Drusilla ashei (12 – 15) and D. nearctica (16 – 19). 12, 16) aedeagus, lateral; 13, 17) aedeagus, parameral; 14, 18) paramere, outer lateral; 15, 19) apex of apical lobe of paramere, inner lateral. Scale bars (0.1 mm): I = 12 – 14, 16 – 18; II = 15, 19." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210862/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
Fig. 
<number box="[288,317,548,572]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
) and parameral (
<figureCitation box="[507,588,548,572]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 19" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[181,1397,421,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[168,1418,411,1895]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 19. Male genitalia of Drusilla ashei (12 – 15) and D. nearctica (16 – 19). 12, 16) aedeagus, lateral; 13, 17) aedeagus, parameral; 14, 18) paramere, outer lateral; 15, 19) apex of apical lobe of paramere, inner lateral. Scale bars (0.1 mm): I = 12 – 14, 16 – 18; II = 15, 19." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210862/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
Fig. 
<number box="[559,588,548,572]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
) view; apical process of median lobe short, extending paramerally; athetine bridge incomplete at aparameral surface, with length of distal apodeme less then four times its width; foramen situated approximately in middle; proximal costa extending most of surface posterior to foramen; median costa extending to apical lobe; arcuate costa sinuate, diverging and closely approximating either side of median costa, again broadly diverging towards apicolateral base of apical lobe. Paramere (
<figureCitation box="[954,1038,692,716]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 19" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[181,1397,421,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[168,1418,411,1895]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 19. Male genitalia of Drusilla ashei (12 – 15) and D. nearctica (16 – 19). 12, 16) aedeagus, lateral; 13, 17) aedeagus, parameral; 14, 18) paramere, outer lateral; 15, 19) apex of apical lobe of paramere, inner lateral. Scale bars (0.1 mm): I = 12 – 14, 16 – 18; II = 15, 19." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210862/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
Fig. 
<number box="[1008,1038,692,716]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
), in outer lateral view, with length approximately two times width; velum large and obscuring apical lobe in outer lateral view; apical lobe of paramere (
<figureCitation box="[270,352,764,788]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 19" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[181,1397,421,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[168,1418,411,1895]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 19. Male genitalia of Drusilla ashei (12 – 15) and D. nearctica (16 – 19). 12, 16) aedeagus, lateral; 13, 17) aedeagus, parameral; 14, 18) paramere, outer lateral; 15, 19) apex of apical lobe of paramere, inner lateral. Scale bars (0.1 mm): I = 12 – 14, 16 – 18; II = 15, 19." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210862/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
Fig. 
<number box="[323,352,764,788]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
) in inner lateral view with four setulae, subequal in length, crowded at apical margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,968]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
Females with vertex of head with shallow impression that is less pronounced than in males; pronotum usual not medially impressed, but when impressed, to a much lesser degree than in males; spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[1267,1350,836,860]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 25" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1468,1491]" captionTargetBox="[164,1418,202,1445]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[158,1428,193,1457]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 25. Details of Drusilla nearctica (20 – 23) and D. ashei (24 – 25). 20) tergite VIII; 21) sternite VIII; 22) female genital segments (tergites IX and X), showing genital plate and spermathecal duct, dorsal; 23) spermatheca; 24) male genital segments (sternite IX and tergites IX and X), dorsal; 25) detail of sternite IX, ventral. Scale bars (0.1 mm): I = 20 – 22, 24 – 25." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210863/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
Fig. 
<number box="[1321,1350,836,860]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
) with a simple bend away from side of spermathecal gland, proximal end bulbous in form, distal end slightly dilated with an internal cone.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1185,943,968]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,968]" box="[199,1185,943,968]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,944,968]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Etymology.</emphasis>
In commemoration, as the first endemic species of 
<taxonomicName box="[912,1005,944,968]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[912,1005,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Drusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the Nearctic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
